                            <comment id="17828356" author="knoguchi" created="Tue, 19 Mar 2024 14:24:39 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;No task metrics available for jobId 0&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is actually failing because Pig is succeeding without running anything. Looking further, found out that Spark is filtering out all input splits and reporting successful empty job results with no metrics.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Setting a flag so that Spark would not ignore PigSplit which looks empty but still have (non-hdfs) inputs. (pig-5448-v01.patch)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
